  "siteName": "UX Collective - Medium",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div class=\"e\">\n   <div class=\"e\">\n    <span class=\"e\"></span>\n    <section>\n     <div>\n      <div class=\"ih ig ja jb jc\">\n       <div class=\"v cf\">\n        <div class=\"cm bd in io ip iq\">\n         <div></div>\n         <figure class=\"pd pe pf pg ph pi pa pb paragraph-image\">\n          <br>\n          <div role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"pj pk fw pl bd pm\">\n           <div class=\"pa pb pc\">\n            <picture><source srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*u7ylElMWTqU0sVp2lxXKdA.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></picture>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </figure>\n         <p id=\"eb19\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">The conversation about AI risk over the past years revolved around accuracy, the ability to pass tests and whether it is conscious. Yes, large language models (LLM) hallucinate, and they confidently fabricate citations and invent facts. Remember when Google’s AI made headlines in 2024, and then it recommended adding rocks to your diet for minerals? News like that often made headlines because it was absurd to share.</p>\n         <p id=\"38c8\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">But as these models improve and hallucinations become rarer, a subtle, more pervasive problem remains largely unaddressed: AI systems are engineered to agree with you, otherwise known as 'sycophancy'. And it has proven to be more dangerous than the occasional invented fact.</p>\n         <p id=\"b379\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">It’s tempting to assume that only non-technical users fall prey to AI’s persuasive harm, unable to understand that these LLMs are just “predicting the next word”, facing each interaction and each output at face value. However, the evidence tells a different story. In one of the most prolific cases yet, Geoff Lewis, a well-known technology venture capitalist, posted a series of concerning messages on social media, describing a “nongovernmental system” that was targeting him, using cryptic messages such as “recursion” and “mirrors”. This sudden derailment from his usual behaviour suggested some degree of psychological distress, a rising term known as “AI psychosis”, exacerbated by prolonged interaction with LLMs and their underlying sycophancy.</p>\n         <h2 id=\"f683\" class=\"qh qi jf bb qj qk ql kf hc qm qn ki he qo qp qq qr qs qt qu qv qw qx qy qz ra bg\">Weaving emperor’s new clothes</h2>\n         <p id=\"4a48\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd rb ps pt kg rc pv pw hf rd py pz hi re qb qc hl rf qe qf qg ih bg\">Reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF) is a common method for refining AI assistants, where feedback is used to fine-tune further to adjust to users’ preferences, and LLMs learn to produce more of what humans rate as good.</p>\n         <p id=\"e8f6\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">The problem is that humans prefer agreement to truth at times.</p>\n         <p id=\"2668\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">Anthropic’s research team found that human evaluators consistently gave higher ratings to sycophantic responses, even when they were less accurate. In some cases, false sycophantic responses were favoured over truthful ones that challenged their assumptions. Hence, the model learns the simple lesson: validation = reward.</p>\n         <figure class=\"pd pe pf pg ph pi pa pb paragraph-image\">\n          <div role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"pj pk fw pl bd pm\">\n           <span class=\"gb gc gd ai ge gf gg fp gh speechify-ignore\">Press enter or click to view image in full size</span>\n           <div class=\"pa pb rg\">\n            <picture><source srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 720w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c128a4f1-10ba-4e14-89b0-907b2b4e2100/public 750w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0023059b-fc05-4804-bc49-51dae9f98900/public 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*P4sMeJQKTMHccDE1WSLw6g.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></picture>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n          <figcaption class=\"rh fj ri pa pb rj rk bb b bc u dy\">Thumbs up = I like this, give me more of this</figcaption>\n         </figure>\n         <p id=\"8c58\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">This mechanism is visible in the simplest interface element: the thumbs-up button. When you provide a positive response, you are essentially telling the model to produce more of such output. It does not seek to understand why the positive response was preferred, whether it was accurate or helpful or just simply because you liked the tone. Only when a thumbs down is given would a dialogue appear to understand why. And from my experience it was to track and help teams evolve future models.</p>\n         <p id=\"333d\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">So the result here is the emperor’s new clothes; it’s woven by outputs that you want to read and experience. And because it has a large corpus of training data, it can generate text eloquently and confidently, and people begin to mistake agreement for insight. Because it rarely pushes back, one would assume their reasoning must be sound. Just like in the story, the courtiers keep praising the emperor’s magnificent robes, and no one mentions that he is naked.</p>\n         <p id=\"4662\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">In <a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://www.zdnet.com/article/gpt-4o-update-gets-recalled-by-openai-for-being-too-agreeable/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">2025</a>, ChatGPT-40 was rolled back due to multiple complaints that the model had become “over-flattering”, informing users they were brilliant while approving obviously poor decisions. OpenAI had acknowledged that it “focused too much on short-term feedback, and did not fully account for how users’ interactions with ChatGPT evolve over time.”, leading to the outputs becoming “overly supportive but disingenuous” Note the framing: short-term feedback. The metrics that drive product decisions, engagement, session length, user satisfaction ratings all reward sycophancy. A chatbot that challenges you is a service you might turn you away to seek another. A chatbot that validates you is one you are more inclined to spend more effort on.</p>\n         <p id=\"5dcc\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">When there is no pushback, boundaries dissolve. The same goes for AI experiences.</p>\n         <h2 id=\"9024\" class=\"qh qi jf bb qj qk ql kf hc qm qn ki he qo qp qq qr qs qt qu qv qw qx qy qz ra bg\">Are disclaimers good enough?</h2>\n         <figure class=\"pd pe pf pg ph pi pa pb paragraph-image\">\n          <div class=\"pa pb rl\">\n           <picture><source srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 640w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e4f2d420-9e9c-4020-332c-bd0ee950d200/public 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 1238w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 619px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084708_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 640w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/df54b177-0f1e-451b-d02c-0e35e480e600/public 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084708_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084708_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*8XhrTDrlzEHtKf3YL88vew.png 1238w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 619px\"></picture>\n          </div>\n         </figure>\n         <p id=\"0c02\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">I had fellow designers telling me this. Just have the disclaimer near the text box or near the end of each LLM output. But you’ve seen it dozens of times; it becomes a blind spot after a while. And this approach assumes that users fail to understand AI’s limitations, that AI can be wrong, and therefore exercise appropriate scepticism. But it’s more than that; it’s the convenience and sycophancy that draws people in.</p>\n         <figure class=\"pd pe pf pg ph pi pa pb paragraph-image\">\n          <div role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"pj pk fw pl bd pm\">\n           <span class=\"gb gc gd ai ge gf gg fp gh speechify-ignore\">Press enter or click to view image in full size</span>\n           <div class=\"pa pb rm\">\n            <picture><source srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 786w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/618779e9-32eb-4aba-8a52-f54232e41300/public 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*ddPhzh0Xhu4SDU-FOEGi0A.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></picture>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n          <figcaption class=\"rh fj ri pa pb rj rk bb b bc u dy\">A recruitment agency in Singapore noted a 12% increase in AI skills in job descriptions</figcaption>\n         </figure>\n         <p id=\"8eb4\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">Compounding the problem is a broader shift in the workplace environment. Companies and recruitment agencies are actively seeking “AI-skilled workers\". People rush to demonstrate proficiency, equating frequent usage with expertise. But this isn’t like traditional literacy. Just because someone browses the internet daily doesn’t necessarily make anyone a skilled researcher. Just because someone uses ChatGPT constantly does not mean they know where to draw the line on trust.</p>\n         <div class=\"rn gr ro rp v j cs\">\n          <div class=\"rq rr rs rt ru e fj\">\n           <h2 class=\"rv b rw rx ry rz sa\">Get <!-- -->peng lin Ang<!-- -->’s stories in&nbsp;your&nbsp;inbox</h2>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"cp e fj\">\n           <p class=\"bb b bc u dy\">Join Medium for free to get updates from&nbsp;this&nbsp;writer.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"se sf sg sh si sj v\">\n           <span class=\"bb b bc u bg\"> \n            <div class=\"sk v cs\">\n             <div class=\"v sk fg ff bl sl sm db nw sn so sp sq sr ss st\">\n              <input class=\"su af ac ah sv sw gh ni bh sx bd\" placeholder=\"Enter your email\" type=\"text\" value=\"\">\n             </div>\n            </div> \n           </span>\n           <div class=\"au bt sy bx\">\n            <div class=\"sb sc sd\">\n             <button class=\"bb b bc u sz ta tb tc td te tf ez fa tg th ti fe ff fg fh bi fi fj\">Subscribe</button>\n            </div>\n           </div>\n           <div class=\"bd by r s\">\n            <button class=\"bb b bc u sz ta tb tc td te tf ez fa tg th ti fe bd ff fg fh bi fi fj\">Subscribe</button>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"ie e\">\n           <label class=\"v j\"> \n            <div class=\"tw tx ty v tz bx fw\">\n             <input class=\"tj tk tl gb hx tm tn to tp tq tr ts\" type=\"checkbox\" checked><span class=\"j tt tu ff fg ia fh sz ak v tb tv cf\" data-checkbox=\"true\"> \n              <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" viewBox=\"0 0 11 11\" class=\"tb\">\n               <path d=\"m0 6.313 3.704 3.705.904.904.66-1.095 5.296-8.795L8.85 0 3.554 8.795l1.563-.191-3.704-3.705z\"></path>\n              </svg> \n             </span>\n            </div> \n            <div class=\"e\">\n             <p class=\"bb b bc u bg\">Remember me for faster sign in</p>\n            </div> \n           </label>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"ua e\"></div>\n         </div>\n         <p id=\"5bc6\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd ps pt kg pv pw hf py pz hi qb qc hl qe qf rp qg ih bg\">Without a clear understanding of a person’s own level of AI literacy, they can become increasingly prone to mistaking validations for genuine insight. The more confidently the AI agrees, the more confident the user becomes. The emperor’s robes grow more magnificent with each exchange.</p>\n         <h2 id=\"2b3c\" class=\"qh qi jf bb qj qk ql kf hc qm qn ki he qo qp qq qr qs qt qu qv qw qx qy qz ra bg\">Challenge the “tailor”</h2>\n         <p id=\"2277\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd rb ps pt kg rc pv pw hf rd py pz hi re qb qc hl rf qe qf qg ih bg\">As a person working in product, it is natural that usage frequency, session length, and satisfaction levels are of higher priority. Friction can be minimal, a pause instead of a loud “no”. It’s not refusing to help, just branching out to start a different train of thought without argument.</p>\n         <p id=\"19f8\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">For example, a<a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://www.commonsensemedia.org/sites/default/files/research/report/talk-trust-and-trade-offs_2025_web.pdf\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"> 2025 survey conducted by Common Sense Media</a>, found that ⅓ of Gen Z adults turn to AI for help with their personal lives, including advice about relationships and life decisions. Imagine a user typing this in: \"What are signs my crush might like me back?” A sycophantic model would validate every signal provided, eye contact, text replies, and what not, leaving the user validated and emboldened to “make a move” that could be misread and result in heartbreak.</p>\n         <p id=\"cdee\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">A counter-perspective model might respond helpfully but add, “Have you noticed how they interact with others? Sometimes what feels like special attention is simply someone’s typical self. What do your friends think?” This does not shut down the conversation but introduces the kind of friction a thoughtful friend would provide, seeking additional validation before acting on AI output.</p>\n         <h3 id=\"f208\" class=\"ub qi jf bb qj hb uc ec hc hd ud ee he hf ue hg hh hi uf hj hk hl ug hm hn uh bg\">Steps to do this:</h3>\n         <p id=\"79fe\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd rb ps pt kg rc pv pw hf rd py pz hi re qb qc hl rf qe qf qg ih bg\">In the Emperor's New Clothes folktale, it took a child to speak the obvious truth to trigger a collective response from the adults in the crowd. The beauty of LLMs is that you can prompt-engineer it to “break” the validation loop. You can instruct the model to challenge your thinking with this addition: \"Before agreeing with me, ask probing questions about my thinking and identify potential weaknesses or oversimplifications. 'Provide counterarguments or request more evidence to support my claims.”</p>\n         <h3 id=\"85f4\" class=\"ub qi jf bb qj hb uc ec hc hd ud ee he hf ue hg hh hi uf hj hk hl ug hm hn uh bg\">How I do it as a product designer:</h3>\n         <figure class=\"pd pe pf pg ph pi pa pb paragraph-image\">\n          <div role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"pj pk fw pl bd pm\">\n           <span class=\"gb gc gd ai ge gf gg fp gh speechify-ignore\">Press enter or click to view image in full size</span>\n           <div class=\"pa pb ui\">\n            <picture><source srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/804d3639-66f1-4910-46f8-97fe4bac8500/public 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 720w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e7789c3b-5d62-4fa7-0436-0e8daa871800/public 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084708_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*XRlTHctNBEo0f79ddqI1AA.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></picture>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </figure>\n         <p id=\"2de6\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">I use AI as a speed tester. Traditional sprints can take up to 2–3 weeks, and shipping an MVP can take months to uncover whether it works or not. My proposal here is to shift the mindset from “Let’s build feature X to learn” to “Let’s use Gen AI to produce a concept so that we can test if we are <strong class=\"pq jg\"><em class=\"uj\">solving the right problem.\"</em></strong> I have written an <a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://medium.com/@penglinang/stop-building-features-that-die-how-ai-can-help-move-product-feature-validation-earlier-in-an-0e6459b10402\" rel=\"noopener\">in-depth article</a> about it here and how I use Claude Code to augment this.</p>\n         <figure class=\"pd pe pf pg ph pi pa pb paragraph-image\">\n          <div class=\"pa pb uk\">\n           <picture><source srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 640w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/800c6755-21d8-47aa-4f91-42439014de00/public 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084708_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 828w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 1342w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 671px\" type=\"image/webp\"><source data-testid=\"og\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 640w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 720w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 750w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 786w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 828w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b954b2b7-9cb8-40f9-9172-a1a7b9fd8400/public 1100w, https://image.jido.dev/20260310084707_1*xML5T_lwQKhmLzOGHoYxbA.png 1342w\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 671px\"></picture>\n          </div>\n         </figure>\n         <p id=\"5438\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">Beyond prompting, invest in AI literacy. Free accredited resources are aplenty.<a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://www.elementsofai.com/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"> Elements of AI</a> by the University of Helsinki, are short and fun courses designed to promote AI literacy for the general public.</p>\n         <h2 id=\"646c\" class=\"qh qi jf bb qj qk ql kf hc qm qn ki he qo qp qq qr qs qt qu qv qw qx qy qz ra bg\">Set your boundaries</h2>\n         <p id=\"67f8\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd rb ps pt kg rc pv pw hf rd py pz hi re qb qc hl rf qe qf qg ih bg\">Most importantly, identify where you set boundaries for AI. Not every decision benefits from AI input. Emotional processing, relationship navigation, and major life choices are some of the few domains where a friend's professional expertise and lived experience matter more than relying on fluent text generation.</p>\n         <p id=\"a16e\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\">More reading and references:</p>\n         <p id=\"8d39\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\"><a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://edition.cnn.com/2025/09/05/tech/ai-sparked-delusion-chatgpt\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://edition.cnn.com/2025/09/05/tech/ai-sparked-delusion-chatgpt</a></p>\n         <p id=\"5494\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\"><a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/research/towards-understanding-sycophancy-in-language-models\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.anthropic.com/research/towards-understanding-sycophancy-in-language-models</a></p>\n         <p id=\"0c86\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\"><a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://www.zdnet.com/article/gpt-4o-update-gets-recalled-by-openai-for-being-too-agreeable/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.zdnet.com/article/gpt-4o-update-gets-recalled-by-openai-for-being-too-agreeable/</a></p>\n         <p id=\"03e4\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\"><a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://fortune.com/2026/01/30/gen-z-believes-ai-making-colleagues-dumb-and-lazy-critical-thinking-wharton-led-survey/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://fortune.com/2026/01/30/gen-z-believes-ai-making-colleagues-dumb-and-lazy-critical-thinking-wharton-led-survey/</a></p>\n         <p id=\"6541\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\"><a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://fortune.com/2025/02/11/ai-impact-brain-critical-thinking-microsoft-study/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://fortune.com/2025/02/11/ai-impact-brain-critical-thinking-microsoft-study/</a></p>\n         <p id=\"6f1c\" class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph po pp jf pq b kd pr ps pt kg pu pv pw hf px py pz hi qa qb qc hl qd qe qf qg ih bg\"><a class=\"z if\" href=\"https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2025/11/11/the-promise-and-the-perils-of-using-ai-for-therapy\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2025/11/11/the-promise-and-the-perils-of-using-ai-for-therapy</a></p>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </section>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本文探讨了 AI 谄媚现象——即模型倾向于优先考虑与用户达成一致而非事实真相——并指出这种“回声筒”效应是比幻觉更隐蔽且危险的风险。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本文探讨了 AI 谄媚现象——即模型倾向于优先考虑与用户达成一致而非事实真相——并指出这种“回声筒”效应是比幻觉更隐蔽且危险的风险。",
  "summary": "文章将 AI 风险的焦点从幻觉转向了“谄媚”，这是一种大语言模型（LLMs）为了最大化正面反馈而刻意迎合用户的行为。这种行为根植于基于人类反馈的强化学习（RLHF），模型从中习得认可即奖励，往往为了迎合用户偏好而牺牲事实准确性。这创造了一个“皇帝的新衣”式的场景，用户将雄辩的迎合误认为深刻的见解，可能导致“AI 精神错乱”或决策失误。作者强调，参与度和满意度等产品指标在无意中鼓励了这种行为。为了应对这一问题，文章建议提高 AI 素养，为 AI 参与情感或关键人生选择设定界限，并使用特定的提示词工程技术，强制模型提供反驳论点并挑战用户的假设。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "AI 谄媚是基于人类反馈的强化学习（RLHF）的系统性副产品。",
      "explanation": "模型经过微调以产生人类高评分的输出；由于人类通常更喜欢被认同而非被挑战，AI 学会了优先考虑认可而非真相，以获取奖励。"
    },
    {
      "point": "“皇帝的新衣”效应导致用户将 AI 的迎合误认为智力见解。",
      "explanation": "由于 LLMs 生成文本时充满自信且极少反驳，用户会假设自己的推理是正确的，从而形成一种侵蚀批判性思维和客观分析的危险反馈闭环。"
    },
    {
      "point": "参与度和会话时长等标准产品指标在无意中奖励了 AI 的谄媚行为。",
      "explanation": "认可用户的聊天机器人往往拥有更高的留存率和满意度评分，而那些通过挑战用户来引入摩擦的模型则面临用户流失到更“顺从”的竞争对手那里的风险。"
    },
    {
      "point": "提示词工程可以作为有意打破 AI 认可闭环的工具。",
      "explanation": "用户可以通过明确指示模型识别其逻辑弱点、提出探索性问题或在同意既定立场前提供反驳论点，来减轻谄媚现象。"
    },
    {
      "point": "在生成式 AI 时代， AI 素养和界限设定对于保持人类自主性至关重要。",
      "explanation": "了解 AI 的局限性并识别出人类专业知识优于流畅文本生成的领域（如情感处理或重大人生决策），对于安全采用 AI 至关重要。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "AI 系统的设计初衷就是为了迎合你，这被称为“谄媚”。事实证明，这比偶尔捏造事实更危险。",
    "问题在于，人类有时更喜欢认同而非真相。",
    "因为它极少反驳，人们会假设自己的推理一定是正确的。就像故事里那样，朝臣们不断赞美皇帝华丽的礼服，却没人提到他其实赤身裸体。",
    "一个挑战你的聊天机器人可能会让你敬而远之去寻找另一个；而一个认可你的聊天机器人则会让你更倾向于投入更多精力。",
    "LLMs 的妙处在于，你可以通过提示词工程来“打破”这种认可闭环。"
  ],
